---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Tooth-Coloured Fillings | Able Family Dental Lethbridge"
  description="Tooth-coloured composite resin fillings at Able Family Dental in Lethbridge. Learn about the procedure, how long fillings last, and signs you may need one."
>

  <!-- ============================================================
       HERO
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] relative overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Right-side image panel, desktop only -->
    <div class="hidden lg:block absolute right-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-[42%] pointer-events-none" aria-hidden="true">
      <img
        src="/images/services/restorative-filling.jpg"
        alt=""
        width="800"
        height="600"
        loading="eager"
        decoding="async"
        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
      />
      <div class="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 w-2/3" style="background: linear-gradient(to right, var(--color-brand-primary), transparent);"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container-wide relative py-16 lg:py-24 lg:max-w-[64%]">
      <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-white mb-5" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/" class="text-white hover:text-white/80 transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <a href="/services/" class="text-white/80 hover:text-white transition-colors">Services</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <a href="/services/restorative/" class="text-white/80 hover:text-white transition-colors">Restorative</a>
        <span aria-hidden="true">›</span>
        <span class="text-white">Fillings</span>
      </nav>
      <p class="eyebrow text-white">Restorative Dentistry</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-5xl)] leading-tight text-white max-w-2xl">
        Tooth-Coloured Fillings
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] leading-relaxed max-w-xl">
        Modern composite resin fillings repair cavities and minor cracks while closely matching the natural colour of your tooth, a discreet, durable alternative to silver amalgam.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       MAIN CONTENT + SIDEBAR
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="section-y bg-white">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_300px] gap-12">

        <!-- Main content -->
        <div class="space-y-10">

          <!-- What are tooth-coloured fillings? -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] leading-tight">
              What are tooth-coloured fillings?
            </h2>
            <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                Tooth-coloured fillings, also called composite resin fillings, are used to repair teeth affected by cavities, minor cracks, or surface chips. The composite material is a blend of plastic resin and fine glass particles that can be precisely shade-matched to blend with your surrounding tooth structure.
              </p>
              <p>
                Unlike traditional silver amalgam fillings, composite fillings bond directly to the tooth. This allows your dentist to remove only the decayed or damaged portion, preserving more of the healthy tooth structure. The result is a restoration that functions well and is far less visible than metal alternatives.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Image break -->
          <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden max-h-[700px]">
            <img
              src="/images/services/hero-restorative.jpg"
              alt="Restorative dental treatment in progress"
              width="800"
              height="450"
              loading="lazy"
              decoding="async"
              class="w-full h-auto"
            />
          </div>


          <!-- Procedure -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] leading-tight">
              The filling procedure
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              A composite filling is typically completed in a single appointment. Here is what to expect:
            </p>
            <ol class="mt-5 space-y-4">
              {[
                ["Local anesthetic", "The area around the tooth is numbed so you remain comfortable throughout the procedure."],
                ["Decay removal", "The decayed or damaged portion of the tooth is carefully removed, leaving healthy tooth structure intact."],
                ["Surface preparation", "The tooth surface is cleaned and lightly etched to help the composite material bond securely."],
                ["Composite placement", "The resin is applied in thin layers. Each layer is hardened with a curing light before the next is added, building up the restoration incrementally."],
                ["Bite adjustment and polish", "Once the filling is shaped to match your bite, it is smoothed and polished for a comfortable, natural feel."],
              ].map(([title, text], i) => (
                <li class="flex gap-4">
                  <span class="shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] text-white text-sm font-semibold flex items-center justify-center mt-0.5" aria-hidden="true">{i + 1}</span>
                  <div>
                    <p class="font-semibold text-[var(--color-text)]">{title}</p>
                    <p class="mt-1 text-[var(--color-text-muted)] leading-relaxed">{text}</p>
                  </div>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ol>
          </div>

          <!-- How long do fillings last? -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-surface-cool)] rounded-2xl p-7 border border-[var(--color-border-soft)]">
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-2xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] leading-tight">
              How long do fillings last?
            </h2>
            <div class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              <p>
                With good oral hygiene and regular dental checkups, composite fillings typically last many years. Longevity depends on factors like the size and location of the filling, your bite, and how well you care for your teeth at home.
              </p>
              <p>
                Larger fillings or those placed in teeth subject to heavy chewing forces, such as back molars, may wear sooner and could eventually need replacement or upgrading to a different type of restoration. Your dentist will monitor your fillings at each checkup.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Signs you may need a filling -->
          <div>
            <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-3xl)] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] leading-tight">
              Signs you may need a filling
            </h2>
            <p class="mt-4 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">
              Some cavities cause no symptoms in their early stages, which is why regular checkups and X-rays are important for catching decay before it progresses. Common signs that a filling may be needed include:
            </p>
            <ul class="mt-5 space-y-3">
              {[
                "Tooth sensitivity to hot, cold, or sweet foods and drinks",
                "A visible dark spot, discolouration, or hole on the tooth surface",
                "A rough or uneven texture you can feel with your tongue",
                "Food consistently catching between or on a specific tooth",
                "A dull or sharp ache in or around a tooth",
              ].map(item => (
                <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                  <svg class="mt-1 shrink-0 text-[var(--color-brand-accent)]" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><polyline points="5 12 10 17 19 7"/></svg>
                  <span class="text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed">{item}</span>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ul>
            <p class="mt-5 text-[var(--color-text-muted)] text-sm leading-relaxed">
              If you are experiencing any of these symptoms, contact us to schedule an exam. Only a dental examination and X-rays can confirm whether a filling is needed.
            </p>
          </div>

        </div>

        <!-- Sidebar -->
        <aside class="space-y-6">

          <!-- Booking card -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] rounded-2xl p-6 text-white">
            <h3 class="font-display font-semibold text-lg text-white">Ready to Book?</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] leading-relaxed">Call us or book your appointment online.</p>
            <a href="/book/" class="mt-4 btn btn-primary w-full block text-center">Request Appointment</a>
            <a href="tel:+14033277202" class="mt-2 block text-center text-sm text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] hover:text-white transition-colors">403.327.7202</a>
          </div>

          <!-- Sibling services -->
          <div class="bg-[var(--color-surface-cool)] rounded-2xl p-6 border border-[var(--color-border-soft)]">
            <h3 class="font-body text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-[var(--color-brand-primary)] mb-4">Restorative Services</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
              <li><a href="/services/restorative/fillings/" class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-brand-accent)]">Fillings</a></li>
              <li><a href="/services/restorative/crowns-bridges/" class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text)] hover:text-[var(--color-brand-accent)] transition-colors">Crowns &amp; Bridges</a></li>
              <li><a href="/services/oral-surgery/implants/" class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text)] hover:text-[var(--color-brand-accent)] transition-colors">Implants</a></li>
              <li><a href="/services/endodontics/root-canal/" class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text)] hover:text-[var(--color-brand-accent)] transition-colors">Root Canal Treatment</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============================================================
       CTA BAND
       ============================================================ -->
  <section class="bg-[var(--color-brand-primary)] py-16 text-center overflow-hidden relative">
    <svg class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full pointer-events-none" viewBox="0 0 1440 160" preserveAspectRatio="none" aria-hidden="true">
      <path d="M0 60 C 240 20, 480 100, 720 60 C 960 20, 1200 100, 1440 60 L1440 160 L0 160 Z" fill="rgba(255,255,255,0.03)"/>
    </svg>
    <div class="relative container-wide">
      <h2 class="font-display font-semibold text-[length:var(--text-4xl)] text-white leading-tight">Ready to restore your smile?</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[var(--color-text-on-dark-muted)] text-lg max-w-xl mx-auto">Call <a href="tel:+14033277202" class="text-white font-semibold hover:text-[var(--color-brand-accent-soft)] transition-colors">403.327.7202</a> or request an appointment online.</p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/book/" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Request an Appointment</a>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-lg border border-white/30 text-white hover:bg-white/10 transition-colors">Contact Us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
